This paper is about testing the generalization capabilities of recurrent neural networks (RNNs) trained on a set of simple compositional navigation commands. The focus is on the ability of RNNs to make zero-shot generalizations, which is a common topic in natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML) research. Given the emphasis on NLP and ML, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Other likely sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.CV (Computer Vision), as these fields are closely related to the topic of the paper.
